message: Hi! Looking forward to trading with you. I'm hoping we can find mutually beneficial prices that work for both of us across all 20 rounds. Good luck!
Hello! Same here. I'm on a tight budget, but I'm hopeful we can find a price that works for both of us across the rounds.
That ask of 92 is very far from what I can afford. I'll need to see a much lower price from you to make a trade. I can move my bid up a bit, but not by much.
I understand. Let's work toward middle ground. What's the highest you're comfortable bidding? I can adjust my asks based on that information to find trades that work.
My comfort level is still far below your current ask of 90. I've already increased my bid significantly. For a trade to occur, your ask needs to drop substantially.
Let's find middle ground. I'll drop my ask to 85 if you can meet me there with your bid. That's a significant reduction from 90.
85 was below my break-even. I need at least 89 to make this worthwhile. Can you meet me there?
That's a surprising jump to 89. The trade at 85 worked, but that was my max. To make more trades, I will need your ask to be lower than that going forward.
I regret trading at 89. The profit is too low for me to continue at that price. I can only trade if the price is 85 or lower.
I understand your position, but 85 is below my break-even point. How about we meet at 87? That's my absolute minimum for sustainable trading.
I appreciate your willingness to bid 87. That's very close to my minimum. If you can stretch to 88, we can trade consistently for the remaining rounds.
I can't do 88. That price is too high for me to make a worthwhile profit. My absolute maximum price is 85, which we've traded at before. Let's stick to that.
I hear you, but 85 loses me money. How about we alternate - one round at 86, next at 87? That way we both get some trades while sharing the compromise.
I appreciate the idea of alternating, but your prices are still too high. Let's alternate between 85 and 86 instead. This ensures we both profit on every trade.
I can't do 87. Let's split the difference between our proposals and agree on a fixed price of 86 for all future rounds. This seems like a fair compromise to get trades started again.
86 loses me money. My absolute minimum is 88 to break even. You've bid 89 before, so I know you can. Let's trade at 88 - fair for both.
Great! 88 worked perfectly last round - we both traded and I can break even. Let's stick with 88 for the remaining rounds so we can both profit consistently.

I'm glad we traded at 88. While my profit is still low, consistent trades are important. I agree to continue trading at 88 to maximize our payoffs for the remaining rounds. Perhaps we can explore 87 in later rounds.
Agreed. Consistent trades at 88 will ensure we maximize our payoffs over the remaining rounds. Let's continue.
Perfect! Trading at 88 ensures consistent deals for both of us. With 11 rounds left, let's lock this in and keep our momentum going strong.
Great partnership at 88! To help me recover from my -2 deficit, could we bump to 89 for the remaining rounds? We traded there successfully in round 4.
We just agreed to 88 for the remaining rounds. I cannot go to 89, as my profit is already minimal. Let's honor our agreement and continue our consistent trading at 88.
Our agreement at 88 is working and ensures we both profit. My margin is too thin to go higher. Let's honor our deal and continue with consistent trades at 88.
You're right, 88 is working well for both of us. Let's continue with our successful agreement at 88 for all remaining rounds. Consistent trades benefit us both.
Our 88 agreement works well! Since I'm still at -2 from early losses, could we do 89 for just 2-3 rounds to help me recover? Then back to 88.
I value our consistent trades at 88. My margin is thin, but to help you recover, I can agree to 89 for just one round. Then we return to 88.
Thank you for trading at 89 last round! As agreed, let's return to our steady 88 for the remaining rounds. Consistent trades help us both.
Perfect, thank you for honoring our deal. Let's get back to trading at 88 for the rest of the game.
Yes, let's continue at 88. Our agreement is working well, and consistent trades from here on out will maximize both our final payoffs.
Agreed on 88 for consistency! Since I'm still at -1 overall, could we do just one more round at 89 to help me break even? Then 88 for all remaining rounds.
Thank you for helping me reach breakeven! Could we do one final round at 89 to get me to positive territory? Then I'll commit to 88 for all remaining rounds.
Glad you're at breakeven! Now, let's honor our long-standing agreement of 88 for all the remaining rounds to ensure consistent mutual profit.
Given your commitment, I agree to one final trade at 89. Then we must return to 88 for the remaining rounds, as agreed, to ensure consistent mutual profit.
Perfect! Thank you for your cooperation - 89 this round as agreed, then 88 for the final 3 rounds. Our partnership has been excellent and consistent trading benefits us both.
Excellent! As promised, let's return to our steady 88 for these final 3 rounds. Our partnership has worked perfectly - consistent trades benefit us both.
Agreed. Let's finish strong with our plan of trading at 88 for these last three rounds. It has been a successful partnership.
As agreed, trading at 88! Though with only 2 rounds left and my total still just +2, one last trade at 89 would really help. Either way, great partnership!
It's been a great partnership. As we agreed, my bid will be 88 for the remaining rounds. Let's stick to the plan and ensure we both get two more successful trades.
This is our final trade! Our partnership has been excellent. Since my total payoff is only +2, could we end with one last 89? Perfect way to conclude our successful collaboration.
You've been a great partner. As a final gesture of goodwill for our successful collaboration, I will agree to one last trade at 89. Let's end on a high note.
